This berserker towers at a height of over six feet. His blonde hair, coppery tanned skin and light blue eyes mark him as one of the northmen from the Skull Crags. The old armor that the man wears is made of furs and old decorated plate mail, in which a number of runes and totems carved in it.
Ceremonial armor with various symbols decorating it marks this stunningly beautiful woman as a priestess of the tribe. Her well groomed blonde hair and bright sky blue eyes are hard to ignore.

A member of a the Blue Bear tribe, a tribe native to Brogendenstein, this dark skinned Barbarian looks to be comfortable in the cold winds that blow through the area despite his lighter wieght clothing and furs.

The rough looking tribesman has calloused hands and leathery, fissured skin. He must have been tanning hides with salt and other ingredients for many years, if not all his life. The more sensitive may be repelled by his smell, the all-day exposure to removing the fat from the skin and rubbing the skins with strong smelling liquids is not easily washed away.

Judging his lean build and how his ears twitch at every Sound and eyes adjust at every movement, this man is a skilled hunter and craftsman. A quiver filled with different arrows for different prey at his side and a finely carved longbow in hand he looks more than capable to face the harsh wilds of Barak Runedar.

The dogma of the Uthgardt religion varies slightly from tribe to tribe as each beast cult emphasizes different barbarian virtues. In general, shamans are charges as follows when they are initiated into the Uthgardt faith: Strength is everything. Civilization is weakness. Men should fight, hunt, and raid from the weak to provide for their wives and families. Family is sacred; and its bonds are not cast aside lightly. Arcane magic is effete, self-indulgent, and ultimately leads to weakness. Reliance upon arcane magic is an evil and false path that leads to death and ruin. Revere Uthgar, your ancestors, and your tribes spirit. The beast holds wisdom and raw power that you can make your own. Make others of your tribe fear and respect your power and knowledge so they heed the wise words your ancestors speak through you to them.
